e Door Remote Wont Work but the Wall Switch Does.";i:3;s:101:"Check the batteries and electrical connections in the remote to make sure they are working correctly.";i:4;s:81:"If they are working correctly the problem might be because of the safety sensors.";i:5;s:85:"Some garage doors have infrared sensors that shoot an invisible beam across the door.";i:6;s:96:"This video from Sears PartsDirect shows what to do if your garage door opener remotes wont work.";i:7;s:116:"We show you a few quick fixes like disabling the lock button eliminating RF interference and checking the batteries.";i:8;s:53:"If remote controls do not work then replace the wire.";i:9;s:69:"If remote controls work reconnect the wires to door control and test.";i:10;s:85:"If remote controls continue to work then there was a loose connection with the wires.";i:11;s:56:"If remote controls do not work replace the door control.";i:12;s:52:"First make sure that the remote batteries are fresh.";i:13;s:70:"Use a battery tester not just a voltmeter or just replace the battery.";i:14;s:103:"Double check that the receiver antenna wire if any is not mangled and has a good connection internally.";i:15;s:69:"If the problem persists it is most likely the receivercontrol module.";i:16;s:274:"When this problem occurs the remotes will not work the door will open but the door will stop reverse immediately after activating the wall button down command or if you are holding the wall button down which bypasses the safety system immediately upon release of the button.";i:17;s:88:"My remote control opens closes the garage door but the button on the wall does not work.";i:18;s:162:"Stack Exchange Network Stack Exchange network consists of 178 QA communities including Stack Overflow the largest most trusted online community for developers to.";i:19;s:60:"A remote will not work if there is no power at the receiver.";i:20;s:118:"Check for Blocked Safety Sensors The safety sensors are located near the bottom rear corners of the garage door track.";i:21;s:84:"How to Fix a Garage Door Opener Remote That Has Stopped Working Check the Batteries.";i:22;s:87:"The most common cause of garage door remote control failure are weak or dead batteries.";i:23;s:27:"Check the Battery Contacts.";i:24;s:37:"Dirty worn or wet contacts inside of.";i:25;s:134:"If that does not work and you know the battery is good then the remote might have lost its programming link to the garage door opener.";i:26;s:56:"Reprogram the remote to activate the garage door opener.";i:27;s:161:"If you cannot reprogram the remote erase all the codes by holding down the Learn button on the motor unit for about 6 seconds or until the Learn light turns off.";i:28;s:45:"Reprogram the remote and see if it works now.";i:29;s:50:"HelpGarage door remote wont work when light is on.";i:30;s:105:"Ive got a weird one going on with my garage door opener and wanted to see if anyone might have any ideas.";i:31;s:122:"I have a Chamberlain Liftmaster Whisper drive garage door opener not sure how old it is was in the house when I bought it.";i:32;s:33:"Thanks to everyone on this forum.";i:33;s:127:"Had a 15 year old Craftsman 12 HP garage door opener that would open with remote and panel but would not close with the remote.";i:34;s:80:"I noticed that the bulb on the garage opener turned on when it opened or closed.";i:35;s:77:"The garage door would only go down using the remote once the bulb turned off.";i:36;s:153:"The first step to solving the problem of a garage door opener remote only working when up close is to find the potential cause of frequency interference.";i:37;s:70:"Begin by troubleshooting for your particular garage door opener model.";i:38;s:38:"In some cases it could be a quick fix.";i:39;s:139:"Wont work If the motor unit has power but wont respond to any remote or the wall control logic board problems could be causing the failure.";i:40;s:76:"Unplug the garage door opener and check the wiring connections on the panel.";i:41;s:32:"Garage Door Opener Losing Range.";i:42;s:94:"There are many reasons that your remote control will only work when it is close to the opener.";i:43;s:51:"Below is a list of some issues that may cause this.";i:44;s:43:"Issues with the wires to the control panel.";i:45;s:61:"Press and hold the button until the led light by it goes out.";i:46;s:60:"This erases all codes from the machine so more can be input.";i:47;s:127:"With remotes in hand press the learn button like a door bell and then the button on the remote and the light bulb should flash.";i:48;s:49:"This tells you that the remote has been accepted.";i:49;s:29:"Repeat for all other remotes.";}}